issues.title: Gullwing Door Strut Failure
issues.description: The hydraulic door struts that support the iconic gullwing doors can fail, causing doors to drop suddenly or fail to stay open. This is a safety hazard and affects the signature feature of the vehicle.
issues.fix_description: Replace hydraulic door struts and seals. Professional installation required due to complexity.
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of door operation, avoid slamming doors, service hydraulic system as recommended

issues.title: Dry Sump Oil System Issues
issues.description: Problems with the dry sump oil system including oil pump failures, scavenge pump issues, and oil tank problems. Can lead to catastrophic engine damage if not addressed.
issues.fix_description: Replace failed oil pumps, repair oil lines, service dry sump tank. Requires specialized AMG service.
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, monitor oil levels frequently, use only specified oil grade

issues.title: SLS AMG Gearbox Actuator Problems
issues.description: The 7-speed dual-clutch transmission actuators can fail, causing harsh shifts, gear selection issues, or complete transmission failure.
issues.fix_description: Replace transmission actuators, update transmission software, fluid service
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, avoid aggressive driving when cold

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Body Panel Delamination
issues.description: Carbon fiber body panels can experience delamination or cracking, particularly around stress points and mounting areas.
issues.fix_description: Repair or replace affected carbon fiber panels, requires specialized bodywork
issues.prevention: Avoid impacts, regular inspection of panel condition, proper storage

issues.title: Exhaust System Overheating
issues.description: The high-performance exhaust system can overheat under extreme conditions, potentially damaging surrounding components or causing heat shields to fail.
symptoms: Excessive heat from rear of vehicle
issues.fix_description: Replace heat shields, inspect exhaust mounting, upgrade cooling if necessary
issues.prevention: Allow proper cool-down after spirited driving, regular exhaust system inspection

issues.title: Electronic Suspension Control Failure
issues.description: The AMG Ride Control suspension system can experience electronic control unit failures or sensor malfunctions, affecting ride quality and handling.
issues.fix_description: Replace suspension control module, update software, replace faulty sensors
issues.prevention: Regular system diagnostics, avoid extreme driving conditions

issues.title: Battery Drain Issues
issues.description: Excessive battery drain when parked due to various electronic modules not entering sleep mode properly, particularly common in early production models.
issues.fix_description: Update software, replace faulty control modules, install battery tender
issues.prevention: Use battery tender when not driven regularly, software updates

issues.title: Air Conditioning Compressor Failure
issues.description: The A/C compressor can fail prematurely, particularly in warmer climates. High-performance driving can accelerate wear.
issues.fix_description: Replace A/C compressor, evacuate and recharge system, replace receiver/drier
issues.prevention: Regular A/C system service, use A/C regularly even in winter

issues.title: Brake System Overheating
issues.description: Under track or aggressive driving conditions, the brake system can overheat, leading to brake fade, rotor warping, or fluid boiling.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake rotors and pads, upgrade brake fluid, inspect brake cooling
issues.prevention: Use high-performance brake fluid, allow cooling between track sessions

issues.title: Engine Mount Deterioration
issues.description: Engine mounts can deteriorate prematurely due to the high torque output of the 6.3L V8 engine, causing excessive vibration and noise.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn engine mounts, inspect transmission mounts
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive launches, warm up engine properly

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: High-pressure fuel pump failures can occur, especially under high-load conditions. Can leave vehicle stranded and potentially damage engine.
issues.fix_description: Replace high-pressure fuel pump, inspect fuel system, update software
issues.prevention: Use high-quality fuel, regular fuel system service

issues.title: Interior Carbon Fiber Trim Cracking
issues.description: Interior carbon fiber trim pieces can develop stress cracks over time, particularly in areas subject to temperature changes.
issues.fix_description: Replace damaged trim pieces, secure loose components
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature exposure, gentle handling of trim

editorial.tagline: Gullwing greatness meets naturally aspirated V8 fury
editorial.hero_blurb: The SLS AMG resurrects the legendary gullwing door design with modern supercar performance. Its hand-built 6.2L V8 delivers 563 horsepower through a soundtrack that defines automotive passion.
editorial.essence: This is Mercedes' love letter to the iconic 300SL Gullwing, wrapped in cutting-edge aluminum construction and powered by AMG's final naturally aspirated masterpiece. The SLS represents the end of an era when supercars prioritized theater over efficiency.
editorial.heritage: Born from the legendary 300SL Gullwing of the 1950s, the SLS AMG revives Mercedes' most iconic design language. It marked AMG's first fully independent supercar development, establishing their capability beyond high-performance sedans.
editorial.design_philosophy: Pure emotional appeal through dramatic gullwing doors, long hood proportions, and aggressive AMG styling. The design team prioritized visual impact and unmistakable road presence over aerodynamic efficiency.
editorial.motorsport_history: Competed in GT3 racing series worldwide with notable success. The SLS GT3 won multiple championships and established AMG's credibility in professional motorsports beyond touring cars.
editorial.engine_character: The 6.2L M159 V8 is a high-revving, naturally aspirated masterpiece that builds power linearly to 7,200 RPM. It delivers immediate throttle response and an intoxicating mechanical symphony that modern turbocharged engines simply cannot match.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 7-speed dual-clutch transmission provides lightning-fast shifts in Race mode while remaining smooth in Comfort. Manual mode offers precise control for enthusiastic driving.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Space-frame aluminum construction creates exceptional rigidity with balanced weight distribution. The chassis rewards smooth inputs but can be unforgiving at the limit, demanding respect and skill.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulic power steering provides excellent feedback and weighting, especially in Sport+ mode. The steering communicates road surface changes clearly while maintaining stability at high speeds.
editorial.brake_confidence: Carbon ceramic brakes deliver exceptional stopping power with excellent pedal feel. Heat management is superb for track use, though initial bite can feel grabby in daily driving.
editorial.sound_signature: A thunderous, metallic roar that crescendos to a banshee wail at redline. The exhaust note is aggressively theatrical with dramatic pops and crackles on overrun.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who value naturally aspirated engines, dramatic styling, and weekend canyon carving over daily practicality. Perfect for collectors seeking the last of AMG's analog supercars.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Daily commuters needing cargo space, fuel economy, or easy entry/exit. The gullwing doors and firm ride make this impractical for regular urban use.
editorial.buyers_summary: Seek low-mileage examples with full service history, as these hand-built engines require proper maintenance. Values are appreciating as collectors recognize this as the end of naturally aspirated AMG supercars.

images.prompt_used:
SUBJECT: Mercedes-AMG SLS AMG (2010-2015), pristine showroom condition.

SETTING: Private collector's industrial warehouse garage. Brick warehouse with arched windows OR modern concrete gallery OR vintage factory with timber beams.

COMPOSITION: Front 3/4 hero angle showing front fascia and driver's side profile. Show COMPLETE car (all four wheels, both bumpers, full roofline). Camera at knee height.

LIGHTING: Golden hour sunlight streaming through large industrial windows. Warm color temperature. Cinematic depth.

TECHNICAL: Magazine-quality automotive photography. Photorealistic, no CGI look. No people, no text, no watermarks, no logos, no license plates.
